    <div class="body">
      Rooting is a vulnerability, but it's also a solution to a dozen larger problems in the Android ecosystem.<br><br>If I didn't have a root exploit for my phone, I'd be locked into a year-old version of Android, and vulnerable to Stagefright and every exploit found in the last year.  For billions of phones, the only way to update a phone is to get around a carrier's or manufacturer's obsolete, locked-down android flavor-- and that means rooting.
      
